1
00:00:23,566 --> 00:00:26,850
You brought this for me to eat. Why are you eating it, Grandma?

2
00:00:45,340 --> 00:00:49,500
You just be a doctor. That's you.

3
00:00:51,660 --> 00:00:56,320
The greatest love that any person can show for another person is sacrifice.

4
00:00:56,320 --> 00:01:01,390
But that sacrifice doesn't make a person great.

5
00:01:05,060 --> 00:01:08,470
Episode 19

6
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:23,860
Now tell me. What did the director say that I did?

7
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:26,750
What did he say that made you, someone who's obsessed with surgeries—

8
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:29,880
I'm not obsessed. Isn't there a nicer way to put it?

9
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:33,240
There's not a more accurate way to put it than that.

10
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:36,470
Why did you give up on something that you love so much?

11
00:01:36,470 --> 00:01:40,300
I won't get hurt. Just tell me the truth.

12
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:45,270
I'm going one step backward and two steps forward. That way Director Jin will relax.

13
00:01:45,270 --> 00:01:46,890
What are you going to go two steps forward with?

14
00:01:46,890 --> 00:01:51,970
I'm looking for Director Jin's weakness right now. As soon as I find it, I'm going to go on the offensive, so don't worry.

15
00:01:52,810 --> 00:01:55,150
There's nothing I can do other than go to work.

16
00:01:55,150 --> 00:02:00,090
It's a relief that you can at least do that. Think optimistically.

17
00:02:00,090 --> 00:02:03,770
Did you know... that you always teach a lesson at the most crucial moment?

18
00:02:03,770 --> 00:02:06,200
A past teacher, presently a doctor,

19
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:09,460
as well as a professor. Do you think my career is going anywhere?

20
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:13,910
If you find his weakness, you have to tell me.

21
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:31,200
Now go home.

22
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:34,660
I can't tell you. It's better for you not to know.

23
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:38,160
Whether it's good or bad, I'll decide. Tell me.

24
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:39,350
I don't know!

25
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:41,820
Are you really going to make me into a fool?

26
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:45,800
Whatever you think of me, before Hye Jeong came along,

27
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:48,880
you were my best friend.

28
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:51,720
Of course, I know you let me off the hook a lot.

29
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:59,730
The reason that Hye Jeong went to your hospital is because of your dad.

30
00:02:59,730 --> 00:03:03,180
- Why?
- Have you seen Hye Jeong's grandmother before?

31
00:03:03,180 --> 00:03:05,950
I have. But I can't really remember.

32
00:03:05,950 --> 00:03:09,170
She passed away while receiving surgery for her cancer.

33
00:03:09,170 --> 00:03:13,150
Your dad did the surgery, and there was medical malpractice.

34
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:14,660
What?

35
00:03:16,650 --> 00:03:21,710
That means, Hye Jeong's grandmother passed away because my dad messed up her surgery?

36
00:03:21,710 --> 00:03:23,300
That's what she believes?

37
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:25,260
She said she found proof a few days ago.

38
00:03:25,260 --> 00:03:26,720
It doesn't make any sense!

39
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:31,390
Do you think she would hold onto something that doesn't make sense for thirteen years?

40
00:03:31,390 --> 00:03:34,390
It's not like Hye Jeong is an idiot.

41
00:03:34,390 --> 00:03:40,040
You know it, too. Her original dream was to start Grandma's Rice Soup.

42
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:43,210
She wanted to live with her grandmother for a long, long time!

43
00:03:45,010 --> 00:03:49,090
It's a misunderstanding. There's no way my dad would've done something like that.

44
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:53,790
Seo Woo!

45
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:02,420
Welcome, Father-in-law.

46
00:04:02,420 --> 00:04:05,380
Why is everyone out here? I just wanted to have a cup of tea.

47
00:04:05,380 --> 00:04:08,250
Father, you came. Of course everyone should come out to greet you.

48
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:11,220
- What about Mother-in-law?
- She's sleeping.

49
00:04:17,140 --> 00:04:19,200
It's honey citron tea.

50
00:04:23,450 --> 00:04:25,980
- What about Seo Woo?
- She's not home yet.

51
00:04:25,980 --> 00:04:28,870
I have something to talk about with Father.

52
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:31,170
Alright.

53
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:39,590
What do you have to tell me?

54
00:04:51,630 --> 00:04:52,720
Are you sick anywhere?

55
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:55,010
What do you mean? It's just stress.

56
00:04:55,010 --> 00:04:58,820
I heard you didn't get your annual health check up last year. Do it.

57
00:04:58,820 --> 00:05:00,800
Alright.

58
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,840
What's troubling you? Tell me.

59
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:07,470
I want to invest more in Sangil Pharmaceuticals, but we don't have enough funding.

60
00:05:07,470 --> 00:05:10,740
We've already invested so much in them already. What's the point of investing more? If you don't have any funds, why bother?

61
00:05:10,740 --> 00:05:12,780
We have to become the strongest shareholder.

62
00:05:12,780 --> 00:05:17,920
Other than the hospital, we need to have a reliable business that can support us.

63
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:19,630
The subsidiary company isn't enough?

64
00:05:19,630 --> 00:05:22,310
We have to give that to Seo Woo.

65
00:05:22,310 --> 00:05:25,330
It looks like the new medicine Sangil Pharmaceuticals is creating is going to be a huge hit.

66
00:05:25,330 --> 00:05:30,060
Then of course, their stock will go up and we can profit manyfold if we purchase their stock.

67
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:34,390
Then I'll supply the funds. What else is a slush fund for?

68
00:05:34,390 --> 00:05:37,160
I really can't live without you, Father.

69
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:40,210
Once the Geriatric Wellness Center is finalized, let's go on a cruise vacation with Mother and everyone.

70
00:05:40,210 --> 00:05:44,190
No thanks. Your stepmother already goes on plenty of vacations.

71
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:50,110
Do you want to see your biological mother? There was no one else like your mother.

72
00:05:50,110 --> 00:05:52,620
Why are you talking about Mom? You're making me miss her.

73
00:05:52,620 --> 00:05:57,770
I have to let you live well and prosperously, so when I meet your dead mother I can lift my head.

74
00:05:59,660 --> 00:06:01,570
Don't worry.

75
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:13,640
Oh, Doctor, why—

76
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:16,100
What are you doing here, Grandmother?

77
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:18,590
I'm the father of the child who's lying down on the bed.

78
00:06:18,590 --> 00:06:22,960
Oh dear, what should I do? I'm so sorry, Doctor.

79
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:27,590
My granddaughter has done something terrible to your daughter.

80
00:06:27,590 --> 00:06:29,500
I'm so sorry.

81
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:33,650
Are you hurt badly? I'm sorry.

82
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,650
Didn't you go home?

83
00:06:46,670 --> 00:06:48,620
Why'd you come back?

84
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:53,230
- Yeong Gook.
- Yeah.

85
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:58,380
Do something terrible to me just once.

86
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:33,670
It's okay.

87
00:07:55,060 --> 00:07:56,550
How's the patient's condition?

88
00:07:56,550 --> 00:07:59,210
Her temperature is at thirty six degrees, it's still normal.

89
00:07:59,210 --> 00:08:00,530
Thank goodness.

90
00:08:00,530 --> 00:08:03,680
The department chief wants everyone to attend the mass conference.

91
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:06,000
Let me see the patient first.

92
00:08:14,980 --> 00:08:18,170
You're really impressive.

93
00:08:27,550 --> 00:08:29,300
Lee Hee Young, twenty nine years old, female.

94
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:33,790
She came into the emergency room from a TA (traffic accident), and her mental state was in a semi-coma GCS (Glasgow Coma Scale) level four.

95
00:08:33,790 --> 00:08:38,840
Looking at her brain CT, it looked like she had about 80cc ( mls ) of ICH (intracranial hemorrhage).

96
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:41,070
It was determined as a result of arteriovenous rupture.

97
00:08:41,070 --> 00:08:44,450
At the time, it was decided that there was no chance of recovery.

98
00:08:44,450 --> 00:08:48,410
As a twenty weeks pregnant woman, we did an emergency surgery to save the child.

99
00:08:48,410 --> 00:08:49,450
How's the baby's condition?

100
00:08:49,450 --> 00:08:51,610
As of now, the baby is growing well without any problem.

101
00:08:51,610 --> 00:08:55,350
Make sure to check the patient's condition carefully. If anything seems strange, we have to deliver the baby immediately.

102
00:08:55,350 --> 00:08:57,400
- Give a heads up to the OB GYN department too.
- Yes.

103
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:00,080
Alright, let's end the conference here for today.

104
00:09:06,030 --> 00:09:09,950
I have something to tell everyone today.

105
00:09:09,950 --> 00:09:15,670
For the past couple of months, there has been a lot going on in the neurosurgery department.

106
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:20,480
A colleague was sick, and a colleague received disciplinary action.

107
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:25,270
Because of the patient who could've been a societal issue. The attention on us wasn't very flattering.

108
00:09:25,990 --> 00:09:31,110
From now on, we might have to endure a hard period for a while.

109
00:09:31,110 --> 00:09:37,860
However, the ones who will endure this hard time will be us.

110
00:09:39,110 --> 00:09:44,960
The neurosurgery department focuses on the brain. The brain powers the entire body.

111
00:09:45,970 --> 00:09:47,000
With that said,

112
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:50,540
neurosurgery department controls everything!

113
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:59,150
Test results

114
00:10:02,770 --> 00:10:08,290
I heard briefly from Doctor Jeong Yoon Do. You're Doctor Yoo Hye Jeong's father?

115
00:10:08,290 --> 00:10:08,990
Ah, yes.

116
00:10:08,990 --> 00:10:11,150
What are your symptoms?

117
00:10:11,150 --> 00:10:13,050
I'm constantly tired.

118
00:10:13,050 --> 00:10:16,660
My upper stomach is in pain. I went to the neighborhood hospital.

119
00:10:16,660 --> 00:10:19,830
They did a blood test and told me to go to a bigger hospital.

120
00:10:21,270 --> 00:10:23,600
Your liver numbers are high.

121
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:26,470
I'll check your eyes. Please open them widely.

122
00:10:27,790 --> 00:10:29,800
Do you drink a lot of alcohol on a regular basis?

123
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:32,170
Yes, I have a little these days.

124
00:10:32,170 --> 00:10:36,160
It doesn't seem like just a little. I think you have a liver infection.

125
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:40,040
- Let's do an ultrasound of your liver.
- Yes

126
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:43,300
But how do you know Doctor Jeon Yoon Do?

127
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:45,210
He's a regular at our restaurant.

128
00:10:45,210 --> 00:10:48,200
He performed a surgery on my wife as well.

129
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:51,690
I think Doctor Jeong is taking care of you because of Doctor Yoo.

130
00:10:51,690 --> 00:10:53,470
Ah, yes.

131
00:10:55,180 --> 00:10:58,070
The detailed statement on the slush fund... Don't you have to submit it to the prosecutor's office?

132
00:10:58,070 --> 00:11:00,050
Things will get wrapped up faster than I thought.

133
00:11:00,050 --> 00:11:01,820
Doctor...

134
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:06,220
I'm sorry, but I can't write up that detailed statement.

135
00:11:06,220 --> 00:11:07,880
Why?

136
00:11:08,780 --> 00:11:11,200
Director Jin is holding Dr. Yoo Hye Jeong as collateral.

137
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,960
Dr. Yoo Hye Jeong...

138
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:20,270
You, you... You're a total lovebird!

139
00:11:20,270 --> 00:11:22,400
Professor...

140
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:28,170
When I heard that the great Dr. Hong volunteered to go to the research center, I sensed that something big must be up.

141
00:11:28,170 --> 00:11:31,110
I can't believe it's for love. Should I congratulate you?

142
00:11:31,110 --> 00:11:33,410
Stop teasing me.

143
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:38,100
I like that you're dating. I hope everything goes well.

144
00:11:39,150 --> 00:11:43,910
But we don't have much time left, Ji Hong.

145
00:11:43,910 --> 00:11:48,640
Once they break ground for the construction of the Geriatric Center, the hospital losses will be enormous.

146
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:51,800
Whoever takes over after Director Jin steps down,

147
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:56,300
the person in that position must start out with a negative balance, a huge burden.

148
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:58,460
That's why I'm deliberating on it.

149
00:12:03,610 --> 00:12:05,300
Look. You over there.

150
00:12:08,230 --> 00:12:10,250
Let's talk for a second.

151
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:28,400
Did you come to this hospital because of my dad?

152
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:33,440
- You're right.
- Are you thinking that my dad comitted malpractice during your grandmother's surgery?

153
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:36,070
It's not a thought; it's a fact. I confirmed it.

154
00:12:36,070 --> 00:12:39,630
How did you confirm it? It was 13 years ago.

155
00:12:39,630 --> 00:12:41,300
There's no way that there's any record left.

156
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:43,770
There was a record.

157
00:12:43,770 --> 00:12:45,610
There's a person who's been keeping it.

158
00:12:45,610 --> 00:12:48,430
Why did they keep it? It's not their record.

159
00:12:48,430 --> 00:12:52,410
There was a reason and it was completely reasonable.

160
00:12:53,620 --> 00:12:56,880
Did you review that record properly? Who reviewed it?

161
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:59,310
By Doctor Jeong Ba Ran.

162
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:04,780
There are things that happen in the surgery room that we cannot control.

163
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:08,280
- You know that too.
- They made a settlement.

164
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:11,980
My dad and the hospital.

165
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:27,480
I came because I have something to ask you.

166
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:32,800
- What is it?
- Did Dr. Yoo Hye Jeong come to you asking you to review an anesthesia record, Uncle?

167
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:36,710
I did. I told her that it was the surgeon's mistake.

168
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:40,300
Does Professor Hong Ji Hong know about this?

169
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:45,180
He probably does because he was the one who introduced me to Doctor Yoo.

170
00:13:45,180 --> 00:13:48,820
Then... Does Sunbae Yoon Do know too?

171
00:13:48,820 --> 00:13:52,600
He does. He likes Doctor Yoo.

172
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:55,850
I've never seen someone fall for someone, alone, so creatively.

173
00:13:57,180 --> 00:13:59,390
Thank you.

174
00:14:12,210 --> 00:14:14,520
Becoming the hospital's director,

175
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:16,470
was it because of Hye Jeong?

176
00:14:17,110 --> 00:14:19,790
- Yeah.
- To help Hye Jeong?

177
00:14:19,790 --> 00:14:24,350
For Dr. Yoo, but Dr. Hong is my neighbor.

178
00:14:25,950 --> 00:14:28,270
You surprise me again and again.

179
00:14:28,270 --> 00:14:32,680
You aren't this kind of person. You don't get involved in others' affairs. You don't take initiative.

180
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:34,610
You don't like management or politics.

181
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:38,090
But if I don't do things like that, how else am I supposed to get close to Doctor Yoo?

182
00:14:38,090 --> 00:14:40,930
Is only getting close to Hye Jeong important?

183
00:14:40,930 --> 00:14:46,650
As for me, I've known you a long time. We have camaraderie.

184
00:14:46,650 --> 00:14:51,120
You've relied on me through tough times, Sunbae. How can you be like this to me?

185
00:14:52,660 --> 00:14:55,840
- I'm sorry.
- If you're sorry then prove it with appropriate actions.

186
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:57,500
What do you want?

187
00:14:57,500 --> 00:15:00,110
Don't make things difficult for my dad.

188
00:15:00,110 --> 00:15:04,620
Being on Hye Jeong's side gives my dad a hard time. Don't do that.

189
00:15:06,300 --> 00:15:08,300
Can you not do it?

190
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:11,690
My dad isn't a bad person.

191
00:15:11,690 --> 00:15:15,100
Hye Jeong's case is a misunderstanding. You understand too, Sunbae.

192
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:19,310
A doctor's job is to save people's lives. But a mistake

193
00:15:19,310 --> 00:15:24,070
can't be helped. None of us are free from it.

194
00:15:42,410 --> 00:15:45,320
Doctor Yoo is pretty.

195
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:49,240
And the professor too. How good looking.

196
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:59,740
Kang Soo, the printer is out of ink.

197
00:15:59,740 --> 00:16:02,700
Hyung, you do it for me. My story is getting really interesting.

198
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:07,490
Hey, if you write everything exactly as it happened, you're plagiarizing. That's plagiarizing Dr. Yoo's life.

199
00:16:07,490 --> 00:16:12,520
C'mon... Hyung Joong Dae, can't you live a life worthy of my plagiarizing?

200
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:15,930
- Wow... You really...
- What are you doing now?

201
00:16:15,930 --> 00:16:19,210
Joong Dae, Ahn Joong Dae, did you take the CT of the patient Lee Choong Hyeon?

202
00:16:19,210 --> 00:16:23,410
- I did.
- You did. Wow, you don't need me nagging anymore these days. You improved a lot.

203
00:16:23,410 --> 00:16:26,040
Wow, without a first year resident, you improved a lot more.

204
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:29,910
I'm about to blow up trying to cover everything including the first year resident's workload.

205
00:16:29,910 --> 00:16:33,040
Hey, what would happen if that body of yours blew up? Who could handle it?

206
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:37,050
Hey, that's your fortune. How would we have known that this would happen to that first year.

207
00:16:37,050 --> 00:16:41,130
Joong Dae, I took the CT of patient Lee Choong Hyeon. Good enough?

208
00:16:42,650 --> 00:16:47,940
It's hard to do alone! It was hard even when Kang Soo was around. Without anyone, could you imagine?

209
00:16:47,940 --> 00:16:50,170
- Are you getting irritated?
- No, that's not it.

210
00:16:50,170 --> 00:16:52,670
We can do it together. We can't select another first year.

211
00:16:52,670 --> 00:16:55,760
There's too much to do for Joon Dae alone.

212
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:58,710
Hyungs, should I help?

213
00:16:58,710 --> 00:17:02,100
Forget it! Just put A4 (8.5" x 11.5") paper in the printer.

214
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:05,320
Hey, put together a night shift schedule. I had to do that.

215
00:17:05,320 --> 00:17:09,140
I didn't know that I'd become your slave after hitting your head a couple of times.

216
00:17:09,140 --> 00:17:10,830
Why do I have to become your slave?

217
00:17:10,830 --> 00:17:13,480
I told you that you'd get hit by a boomerang.

218
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:16,080
I learned this time that there really is a boomerang.

219
00:17:16,080 --> 00:17:19,550
Joon Dae, Joon Dae, Ahn Joon Dae! This kid really...

220
00:17:19,550 --> 00:17:22,660
- How can you be joking?
- If Joong Dae leaves

221
00:17:22,660 --> 00:17:26,670
Chief you and I will have to do all of the work of the first-year residents.
- That's right, that's right.

222
00:17:27,490 --> 00:17:30,840
I was going to say that I like Joon Dae Joon Dae Ahn Joon Dae.

223
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:32,840
I like you without others knowing.

224
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:37,240
You want A4 paper? Hyung, you want a schedule? Okay.

225
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:39,060
I like you without others knowing.

226
00:17:39,060 --> 00:17:42,560
- Comrade one! Go!
- Comrade two!

227
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:44,450
- I like you.
- Okay.

228
00:17:44,450 --> 00:17:47,580
I don't like you though. He's mistaken.

229
00:17:58,220 --> 00:18:00,000
Yes, Doctor.

230
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,030
Your father's results came out.

231
00:18:02,030 --> 00:18:03,470
What?

232
00:18:03,470 --> 00:18:09,670
He got an examination from me. I called you to let you know first because I thought you'd be worried.

233
00:18:09,670 --> 00:18:11,420
It seems like you didn't know.

234
00:18:16,640 --> 00:18:21,920
The ultrasound shows that you have fatty liver disease. From that, you developed hepatitis.

235
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,940
