482
00:38:41,830 --> 00:38:45,340
The money's not the issue. Get him out right away!

483
00:38:51,830 --> 00:38:56,200
What are you going to say? You called me to comfort me.

484
00:38:56,970 --> 00:39:01,850
Trying to comfort you won't work. You've never gone through something like this, right?

485
00:39:04,920 --> 00:39:07,800
I've been through it twice.

486
00:39:10,700 --> 00:39:12,450
Thank you.

487
00:39:17,850 --> 00:39:20,590
Dad.

488
00:39:43,740 --> 00:39:45,450
How is Yoo Hye Jeong doing?

489
00:39:45,450 --> 00:39:47,180
Did you call me to ask me that?

490
00:39:47,180 --> 00:39:50,770
Hong Ji Hong gave us a huge news issue to deal with. You think I'll just stand back and watch?

491
00:39:50,770 --> 00:39:55,310
When he sees Yoo Hye Jeong be whispered about on the lips of others, and in the media, he'll realize something then.

492
00:39:55,310 --> 00:39:57,770
How are you going to put Yoo Hye Jeong up and about in the media?

493
00:39:57,770 --> 00:40:01,840
I hid a voice transcript, but it disappeared. I'm sure it'll turn up when I look for it.

494
00:40:02,690 --> 00:40:04,830
I got rid of it.

495
00:40:04,830 --> 00:40:05,790
What?

496
00:40:05,790 --> 00:40:11,330
When I heard about the medical malpractice, I automatically took your side because you're my dad.

497
00:40:11,330 --> 00:40:14,360
Because it felt like your mistakes would become my own, I avoided it.

498
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:16,780
I didn't do anything wrong! She's just overreacting!

499
00:40:16,780 --> 00:40:20,670
Is it normal that she came to our hospital for an incident that ended with a settlement 13 years ago?

500
00:40:20,670 --> 00:40:22,020
It's not normal.

501
00:40:22,020 --> 00:40:26,430
If it was me and the same thing happened to you, I would've ripped and killed you on the spot.

502
00:40:26,430 --> 00:40:29,780
Why'd you do it? If you made a mistake, you could've just apologized.

503
00:40:29,780 --> 00:40:31,250
Why did you make a person's heart hurt?

504
00:40:31,250 --> 00:40:35,320
Say I apologized. Do you know many people would come to take money because of that?

505
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:37,870
Just what kind of life have you led, Dad?

506
00:40:37,870 --> 00:40:41,930
Have you only ever met people like that? Have you never met any good people?

507
00:40:41,930 --> 00:40:44,230
Are all the people in the world those kinds of weird people?

508
00:40:44,230 --> 00:40:47,170
Do you choose to treat people based on that standard?

509
00:40:48,500 --> 00:40:51,790
I'm ashamed of you, Dad! I'm ashamed!

510
00:40:51,790 --> 00:40:55,610
I'm ashamed of myself! I'm embarrassed!

511
00:40:55,610 --> 00:40:57,750
Don't listen to what others are saying.

512
00:40:57,750 --> 00:41:00,420
It'll all end soon. Your grandfather will come out as well.

513
00:41:00,420 --> 00:41:02,790
Do you know what Hye Jeong's dream is?

514
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:06,660
It was to provide her grandma with a life of comfort.

515
00:41:06,660 --> 00:41:09,500
To graduate from school and work at her grandmother's.

516
00:41:09,500 --> 00:41:13,590
To live with her grandmother, just that one thing.

517
00:41:14,490 --> 00:41:16,670
Dad, why couldn't you understand her heart?

518
00:41:16,670 --> 00:41:21,080
Dad, at that time, if you had just apologized and said you tried your best. Because you couldn't say that much,

519
00:41:21,080 --> 00:41:27,280
I know that what you lost is very precious. If you'd said that, she wouldn't have gone this far.

520
00:41:46,360 --> 00:41:48,370
Did you place patient Song Jin Yeong in ICU?

521
00:41:48,370 --> 00:41:51,870
For now, do a follow-up CT and let me know immediately if she gains consciousness.

522
00:41:51,870 --> 00:41:53,540
Yes.

523
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:55,950
Hello!

524
00:41:55,950 --> 00:41:59,480
Oh, what are you doing here, Professor? Hello.

525
00:41:59,480 --> 00:42:01,080
Am I not allowed to come by?

526
00:42:01,080 --> 00:42:04,170
Of course, you can! You came here to see Doctor Yoo Hye Jeong right.

527
00:42:04,170 --> 00:42:05,870
Me? Who said so?

528
00:42:05,870 --> 00:42:07,870
Everybody already knows!

529
00:42:07,870 --> 00:42:09,220
What do they know?

530
00:42:09,220 --> 00:42:10,760
About you two!

531
00:42:10,760 --> 00:42:13,370
Professor, there's something I want to ask.

532
00:42:13,370 --> 00:42:16,200
Is that so? Let's go talk and talk about it then, Doctor Yoo.

533
00:42:19,230 --> 00:42:21,280
You don't think they're under the impression that we have no idea, do you?

534
00:42:21,280 --> 00:42:26,290
That's not possible. If they think so, then they're both blind.

535
00:42:29,180 --> 00:42:31,280
If you do this, people are going to find out.

536
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:34,120
We've already been caught. Can't you tell from people's expressions?

537
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:38,490
Anyway, if Chief knows, it's the same as everyone knowing.

538
00:42:38,490 --> 00:42:41,830
Still, shouldn't we act like we don't know?

539
00:42:41,830 --> 00:42:42,970
Why?

540
00:42:42,970 --> 00:42:45,040
To make it fun.

541
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:47,440
Okay, let's do that.

542
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:51,460
But aren't you too laid back, Doctor? Will you continue to be at the research center?

543
00:42:51,460 --> 00:42:53,160
That's up to the director's will.

544
00:42:53,160 --> 00:42:55,210
You can say you want to come back.

545
00:42:55,210 --> 00:42:59,820
Aren't you hungry? I'm a little hungry. I want some cold noodles before I go home. Should we get some now?

546
00:42:59,820 --> 00:43:03,180
- Don't do stuff like this.
- What's "stuff like this"?

547
00:43:03,200 --> 00:43:08,460
Changing the subject when you're in a bind. You can't make a move because of my voice transcript, right?

548
00:43:08,460 --> 00:43:11,140
You're someone who really needs to go until the end, huh?

549
00:43:11,140 --> 00:43:12,840
Yes.

550
00:43:13,780 --> 00:43:15,400
You're right. I can't move because I'm being wary of you.

551
00:43:15,400 --> 00:43:19,160
But, if the chief director gets dismissed, the hospital director will change too.

552
00:43:19,160 --> 00:43:22,000
I'm going to stay still, since they're mad.

553
00:43:22,940 --> 00:43:25,140
Scaredy-cat.

554
00:43:27,190 --> 00:43:29,270
One moment. Jin Seo Woo.

555
00:43:30,410 --> 00:43:32,200
Yeah?

556
00:43:32,200 --> 00:43:36,450
You're on duty today, right? I have something to tell you. Come see me for a bit.

557
00:43:36,450 --> 00:43:40,880
I'm sorry I can't. I'm with someone right now.

558
00:43:40,880 --> 00:43:43,240
It's because it's something important.

559
00:44:04,240 --> 00:44:06,750
Your dad said to give this to me?

560
00:44:06,750 --> 00:44:09,960
No. I stole it.

561
00:44:12,010 --> 00:44:16,340
Your grandma, I've met her.

562
00:44:16,340 --> 00:44:20,790
When I was hospitalized, she came by with juice.

563
00:44:20,790 --> 00:44:23,830
Not concentrate. 100% juice.

564
00:44:25,430 --> 00:44:28,420
There was never a time when I considered you a rival.

565
00:44:28,420 --> 00:44:33,630
My 100% friendliness was because I didn't consider you a rival.

566
00:44:34,440 --> 00:44:37,030
Whatever the reason, kindness is kindness.

567
00:44:37,030 --> 00:44:41,460
I didn't want to acknowledge that you were a better kid than me.

568
00:44:42,940 --> 00:44:45,980
I think that's when my tragic story started.

569
00:44:48,210 --> 00:44:50,870
I provoked you.

570
00:44:52,010 --> 00:44:56,900
I didn't know back then, because it was before I was in the category of "rival."

571
00:44:58,450 --> 00:45:00,010
I'm sorry.

572
00:45:03,770 --> 00:45:09,350
I had a chance when Soon Hee came looking for me.

573
00:45:09,350 --> 00:45:13,930
I justified it and thought time would take care of it.

574
00:45:14,830 --> 00:45:18,320
But the reality became worse than back then.

575
00:45:18,320 --> 00:45:23,380
♫  Don't be in pain saying you are lonely  ♫

576
00:45:23,380 --> 00:45:25,330
I thought that now is the opportunity.

577
00:45:25,330 --> 00:45:32,540
♫  Oh, if I find that path  ♫

578
00:45:32,560 --> 00:45:35,970
♬  Will I be able to laugh? ♬

579
00:45:35,970 --> 00:45:38,010
Seo Woo!

580
00:45:38,010 --> 00:45:45,390
I'm sorry. I'll apologize in my dad's place.
♬  Someday when . ♬

581
00:45:45,390 --> 00:45:49,450
♫  Tell me to cheer up and thank me  ♫

582
00:45:49,450 --> 00:45:51,690
♫  and that I will be okay  ♫

583
00:45:51,690 --> 00:45:53,810
♫  Tell me  ♫

584
00:45:53,810 --> 00:45:57,470
♫  Lalala lalala  ♫

585
00:45:57,470 --> 00:46:00,310
♫  I will cherish myself more  ♫

586
00:46:00,310 --> 00:46:04,480
♫  Lalala lalala  ♫

587
00:46:04,480 --> 00:46:08,640
♫  I love myself  ♫

588
00:46:08,640 --> 00:46:10,060
Did the talk go well?

589
00:46:10,060 --> 00:46:11,650
Yes.

590
00:46:17,200 --> 00:46:21,440
I think not hating her this whole time was a good thing.

591
00:46:24,230 --> 00:46:26,780
Hye Jeong, let's get married.

592
00:46:26,780 --> 00:46:27,930
What?

593
00:46:27,930 --> 00:46:30,430
Why? You don't want to?

594
00:46:30,430 --> 00:46:34,690
I mean... Aren't you being too harsh?

595
00:46:34,690 --> 00:46:36,140
What?

596
00:46:36,140 --> 00:46:40,520
It's not like marriage is a joke. How could you blurt it out like that?

597
00:46:40,520 --> 00:46:43,790
I didn't just blurt it out, I said it because it was something I've been thinking about.

598
00:46:43,790 --> 00:46:45,980
But this isn't right.

599
00:46:45,980 --> 00:46:48,470
That's not being romantic!

600
00:46:48,470 --> 00:46:51,140
I thought that you didn't like that kind of stuff.

601
00:46:51,140 --> 00:46:52,280
Why would I hate it?

602
00:46:52,280 --> 00:46:55,170
That's right. Why did I think you'd hate it?

603
00:46:55,170 --> 00:46:56,590
I don't hate it.

604
00:46:56,590 --> 00:46:58,390
What should I do? Should I do it again?

605
00:46:58,390 --> 00:47:00,270
Yes.

606
00:47:00,270 --> 00:47:02,960
Isn't there something for you to do for me?

607
00:47:05,380 --> 00:47:10,980
That's right. It's not because I really want to hear those words because I know your heart either way,

608
00:47:10,980 --> 00:47:15,380
but a person should live while expressing herself.

609
00:47:16,680 --> 00:47:19,890
I'm not going to.

610
00:47:19,890 --> 00:47:24,340
Today doesn't have the right atmosphere. The lights should be a little dimmer and...

611
00:47:24,340 --> 00:47:26,560
Hey! You're kind of funny.

612
00:47:26,560 --> 00:47:29,980
♫  You are the reason I live  ♫

613
00:47:29,980 --> 00:47:32,970
♫  It's an unexplainable miracle  ♫

614
00:47:32,970 --> 00:47:34,440
I'm happy.

615
00:47:34,440 --> 00:47:37,560
You're coming in without warning again.

616
00:47:37,560 --> 00:47:44,620
I'm keeping myself from the next action because we're at the hospital.

617
00:47:44,620 --> 00:47:50,880
♫  Take another step closer  ♫

618
00:47:51,930 --> 00:47:56,300
♫  Yes I believe my destiny  ♫

619
00:47:56,300 --> 00:47:58,180
Hello.

620
00:48:01,760 --> 00:48:05,780
Director, Professor Hong wants to meet with you.

621
00:48:15,340 --> 00:48:20,280
I liked you, Professor Hong, but I didn't know that you would stab me in the back like this.

622
00:48:20,280 --> 00:48:21,410
I'll reinstate you.

623
00:48:21,410 --> 00:48:26,470
It seems like because Chief Director Jin is in prison, you think that the world is yours, but don't mistake yourself.

624
00:48:26,470 --> 00:48:29,100
I have Dr. Yoo Hye Jeong's voice recording.

625
00:48:29,100 --> 00:48:31,570
There's no reason for me to accept your will anymore.

626
00:48:31,570 --> 00:48:35,250
But I will respect you because you are still the director.

627
00:48:35,250 --> 00:48:38,870
My return should be after your leave, right director?

628
00:48:38,870 --> 00:48:41,090
Then you might not be able to return forever.

629
00:48:41,090 --> 00:48:44,420
Then things wouldn't have gone your way.

630
00:48:44,420 --> 00:48:46,950
I hope at least that will go well.

631
00:48:57,710 --> 00:49:00,600
Dr. Yoo Hye Jeong has been waiting for you.

632
00:49:08,500 --> 00:49:11,020
I just came from meeting with Professor Hong.

633
00:49:11,020 --> 00:49:14,760
Are you two a team fighting the battle separately?

634
00:49:15,630 --> 00:49:17,890
I'm going to stop now.

635
00:49:17,890 --> 00:49:21,240
I take back all the curses I spewed on you.

636
00:49:21,240 --> 00:49:22,940
What are you doing right now?

637
00:49:22,940 --> 00:49:25,820
It was a hard decision for me.

638
00:49:25,820 --> 00:49:28,710
From now on, I'm going to live without having any ties to you.

639
00:49:29,400 --> 00:49:33,670
Since I started, I thought I should see it to the end so I came to finish things up.

640
00:49:33,670 --> 00:49:35,130
Did you want to hear me say thank you?

641
00:49:35,130 --> 00:49:37,540
No. Please don't do it.

642
00:49:37,540 --> 00:49:39,380
You just stay put.

643
00:49:39,380 --> 00:49:43,360
I'm just finishing my homework right now.

644
00:49:44,210 --> 00:49:47,730
I've learned a lot during my homework.

645
00:50:01,660 --> 00:50:03,790
What was that?

646
00:50:08,510 --> 00:50:13,040
Director, the chief director has been released on bail, so you should go.

647
00:50:13,040 --> 00:50:15,330
I know. Let's go.

648
00:50:22,610 --> 00:50:25,620
What brings you here? Are you looking for Hye Jeong?

649
00:50:25,620 --> 00:50:29,730
- I'm here for you. Let's go out to eat.
- I don't want to.

650
00:50:29,730 --> 00:50:33,210
You always don't eat whenever you're in a bad mood. Come on, get up.

651
00:50:33,210 --> 00:50:37,360
If you're just paying me back for when I comforted you, you don't have to do this.

652
00:50:37,360 --> 00:50:43,050
I wouldn't be doing this just to pay you back. I'm doing this because I want to.

653
00:50:43,050 --> 00:50:46,800
Seo Woo— Hello.

654
00:50:46,800 --> 00:50:48,710
Oh, you're here?

655
00:50:49,530 --> 00:50:53,210
I came to eat with Seo Woo...

656
00:50:53,210 --> 00:50:55,010
Alright, let's go.

657
00:50:55,890 --> 00:50:59,390
Hey! You said you didn't want to when I asked.

658
00:50:59,390 --> 00:51:02,980
I choose who I get to eat with.

659
00:51:02,980 --> 00:51:06,420
Yeah, it's up to you. Go on and eat with Yeong Gook,

660
00:51:06,420 --> 00:51:08,080
but you're a bit rude.

661
00:51:08,080 --> 00:51:11,030
Compared to how rude you were to me, this is nothing.

662
00:51:11,030 --> 00:51:14,080
Did I say anything about what I did to you? I'm just telling you about you.

663
00:51:14,770 --> 00:51:19,290
I feel at ease. Take her out and treat her to something delicious.

664
00:51:19,290 --> 00:51:22,530
Go eat something expensive, I'll pay you back.

665
00:51:27,870 --> 00:51:29,610
Pretending as if he's cool.

666
00:51:29,610 --> 00:51:33,150
He's not pretending to be cool; he is cool. If you like him, do so.

667
00:51:33,150 --> 00:51:35,420
Don't block your feelings from going anywhere.

668
00:51:35,420 --> 00:51:37,680
It's not like that.

669
00:51:37,680 --> 00:51:42,400
I just feel bad. I keep remembering the times I acted like a fool.

670
00:51:43,370 --> 00:51:44,880
A fool?

671
00:51:47,610 --> 00:51:49,990
Mom

672
00:51:49,990 --> 00:51:51,890
Seo Woo, it's been a while.

673
00:51:51,890 --> 00:51:54,270
Yes, Grandfather. It was hard, wasn't it?

674
00:51:54,270 --> 00:51:55,980
I'm fine now. Let's eat.

675
00:51:55,980 --> 00:51:58,720
Father, have some of this.

676
00:52:00,760 --> 00:52:06,190
Ah, what's wrong with you? That's why I told you to have a medical check-up.

677
00:52:06,190 --> 00:52:09,310
It's just because of stress. Why are you forcing me to have an illness?

678
00:52:09,310 --> 00:52:12,880
Wait, you still didn't receive your medical check-up?

679
00:52:12,880 --> 00:52:15,000
I'll go, since you're back now...

680
00:52:15,000 --> 00:52:18,940
Seo Woo, book an appointment for your father's check-up.

681
00:52:18,940 --> 00:52:19,900
I understand.

682
00:52:19,900 --> 00:52:24,800
- From now on, it'll be a big fight. Health is the most important.
- Yes.

683
00:52:24,800 --> 00:52:27,500
- Seo Woo, let's eat.
- Yes.

684
00:52:29,100 --> 00:52:31,700
- Father-in-law, please eat a lot.
- All right.

685
00:52:39,720 --> 00:52:43,680
Doctor Yoo Hye Jeong, is Professor Hong not going to return?

686
00:52:43,680 --> 00:52:47,740
There's a procedure for it. The director has to give his approval.

687
00:52:49,500 --> 00:52:53,600
- Ah, Father is coming today.
"Father"?

688
00:52:53,690 --> 00:52:56,840
Your father has an appointment with my uncle today.

689
00:52:56,840 --> 00:52:59,260
I went to the Rice Soup Restaurant a three days ago.

690
00:52:59,260 --> 00:53:03,480
The rice soup was good. I heard that your grandma used to run that place.

691
00:53:03,480 --> 00:53:05,060
Yes.

692
00:53:09,520 --> 00:53:11,640
Doctor Jin.

693
00:53:11,640 --> 00:53:14,670
Patient Kim Jin Gyeong. Did you change the nimodipine to oral medication and is she ambulating?

694
00:53:14,670 --> 00:53:17,720
Yes, we started wheelchair ambulation yesterday.

695
00:53:17,720 --> 00:53:19,300
I need to visit.

696
00:53:19,300 --> 00:53:20,850
Yes.

697
00:53:24,170 --> 00:53:27,550
There's no reason for you to be dispirited because of what's happening between your father and me.

698
00:53:27,550 --> 00:53:29,500
The reason I chose you as a fellow for our department

699
00:53:29,500 --> 00:53:32,880
is because you were the right person.

700
00:53:32,880 --> 00:53:34,830
Thank you.

701
00:53:39,130 --> 00:53:40,720
Take the call.

702
00:53:47,210 --> 00:53:48,490
Yes?

703
00:53:55,720 --> 00:53:56,760
This is Kim Tae Ho speaking.

704
00:53:56,760 --> 00:53:59,570
Vice Director, this is Lee Gi Won from Wellness Center.

705
00:53:59,570 --> 00:54:03,270
I'm calling due to Director Jin Myeong Hoon's medical check-up results.

706
00:54:03,270 --> 00:54:05,500
What is it?

707
00:54:27,150 --> 00:54:29,500
Yes.

708
00:54:29,500 --> 00:54:30,950
Look at this.

709
00:54:34,710 --> 00:54:36,470
There are tumors on vertebrae three and four.

710
00:54:36,470 --> 00:54:39,350
It's either ependymoma or astrocytoma, right?

711
00:54:39,350 --> 00:54:44,490
This is serious. If it's this bad, then the symptoms must have shown up. Who is this?

712
00:54:45,200 --> 00:54:49,550
Director Jin Myeong Hoon. This will be a hard surgery.

713
00:54:49,550 --> 00:54:53,470
Even if we do the surgery, I don't think the prognosis will be good.

714
00:54:53,470 --> 00:54:56,220
I'm a surgeon who can accomplish most things if I set my mind to it,

715
00:54:56,220 --> 00:54:58,830
but this is a hard surgery, even for me.

716
00:54:58,830 --> 00:55:00,720
Of course.

717
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:05,530
Still, you're the only one who can do this surgery.

718
00:55:27,500 --> 00:55:28,840
Yeah, Seo Woo?

719
00:55:28,840 --> 00:55:31,970
Mom, Dad's results came out.

720
00:55:31,970 --> 00:55:34,660
It's not something bad, right?

721
00:55:34,660 --> 00:55:36,790
It's a tumor.

722
00:55:48,480 --> 00:55:50,660
It's been a while.

723
00:55:50,660 --> 00:55:52,190
How is your health?

724
00:55:52,190 --> 00:55:54,130
It's fine.

725
00:55:55,350 --> 00:55:57,800
Do you visit Doo Sik often?

726
00:55:57,800 --> 00:55:59,540
I visit at least once a month.

727
00:55:59,540 --> 00:56:03,850
I see. I need to visit him too.

728
00:56:03,850 --> 00:56:06,410
He was my lifelong friend.

729
00:56:06,410 --> 00:56:09,370
I regret not being with him at the end.

730
00:56:13,790 --> 00:56:18,810
Can't you perform the surgery on my Myeong Hoon?

731
00:56:18,810 --> 00:56:20,790
Well, I'm at the research center right now.

732
00:56:20,790 --> 00:56:23,900
You can just come back. That's not hard.

733
00:56:23,900 --> 00:56:27,580
Director Jin will refuse to undergo a surgery performed by me.

734
00:56:27,580 --> 00:56:30,390
- Leave that to me.
- In a surgery,

735
00:56:30,390 --> 00:56:33,750
it's a given that the doctor has to do well, but the patient has to do well too.

736
00:56:33,750 --> 00:56:36,510
He sees me as his rival.

737
00:56:38,460 --> 00:56:43,620
He won't be able to leave himself comfortably to me, and if that happens, the success rate drops.

738
00:56:44,290 --> 00:56:47,420
On top of that, this surgery has a high-risk factor,

739
00:56:47,420 --> 00:56:50,940
so the success rate for the surgery itself is low.

740
00:56:52,020 --> 00:56:57,910
Still, I beg of you because the doctor has to do much better than the patient.

741
00:57:04,680 --> 00:57:07,700
Surgical Management of Intramedullary Spinal Ependymomas

742
00:57:36,710 --> 00:57:39,970
Patient Kim Soo Ryeon's carvenous angioma,

743
00:57:39,970 --> 00:57:42,170
did you schedule the surgery?

744
00:57:42,170 --> 00:57:45,090
Not yet. Why?

745
00:57:45,090 --> 00:57:49,290
That's a tough surgery. I was wondering if Dr. Hong can do it.

746
00:57:49,290 --> 00:57:52,220
The chief is good too.

747
00:57:53,110 --> 00:57:56,440
Would Doctor Hong have lost his skills because he hasn't performed surgery recently?

748
00:57:56,440 --> 00:57:58,910
He hasn't lost his skills.

749
00:57:58,910 --> 00:58:02,060
He practically spends all of his time watching videos of surgeries.

750
00:58:02,060 --> 00:58:04,940
He has quick hands and he's precise.

751
00:58:08,070 --> 00:58:12,240
When you heard that your grandma had cancer, how did you feel?

752
00:58:13,910 --> 00:58:18,160
I first heard that news in the visiting room of the holding cell I was locked up in.

753
00:58:18,160 --> 00:58:20,490
I felt as if the heavens were falling.

754
00:58:21,300 --> 00:58:24,660
My grandma was my refuge in my life.

755
00:58:25,350 --> 00:58:28,050
I cried and cried again.

756
00:58:31,730 --> 00:58:35,080
I hated myself for not being able to do anything.

757
00:58:35,730 --> 00:58:39,850
If only I had done a little better, my grandma wouldn't have been sick.

758
00:58:46,660 --> 00:58:48,620
What's wrong with you?

759
00:58:51,070 --> 00:58:54,050
My dad was really good to me.

760
00:58:55,010 --> 00:58:57,870
I have many memories with him when I was young.

761
00:58:59,690 --> 00:59:01,510
Is something going on?

762
00:59:02,540 --> 00:59:07,620
Of course, our relationship is strained these days because he has high expectations.

763
00:59:10,610 --> 00:59:14,650
Until recently, I hated him, didn't listen to him,

764
00:59:14,650 --> 00:59:17,050
and didn't even go home often.

765
00:59:26,700 --> 00:59:27,630
Yeah, what is it?

766
00:59:27,630 --> 00:59:31,550
There's a male patient in the ER. I think he feel asleep after taking sleeping pills.

767
00:59:31,550 --> 00:59:35,750
What are you doing? Why are you reporting to me about a patient who took sleeping pills?

768
00:59:35,750 --> 00:59:37,520
It's Director Jin Myeong Hoon.

769
00:59:37,520 --> 00:59:41,570
His wife says a tumor was discovered from a recent physical.

770
00:59:50,810 --> 00:59:53,460
I'll be down soon so call Doctor Hong Ji Hong.

771
00:59:53,460 --> 00:59:55,070
Yes.

772
01:00:07,190 --> 01:00:08,270
Are you okay, Honey?

773
01:00:08,270 --> 01:00:12,150
Ah, why are you creating such a fuss?! Why did you bring someone who was just sleeping to the emergency room?!

774
01:00:13,930 --> 01:00:15,780
Are you okay?

775
01:00:15,850 --> 01:00:19,750
I'm fine. I'm so embarrassed because of your mom!

776
01:00:19,790 --> 01:00:22,830
So, why didn't you get admitted to the hospital when I told you to?

777
01:00:22,830 --> 01:00:25,830
If you had been hospitalized after you found out about your illness, this wouldn't have happened.

778
01:00:25,830 --> 01:00:28,100
- I'll examine you.
- Ah,

779
01:00:28,100 --> 01:00:30,500
forget it. Let's do it later.

780
01:00:35,780 --> 01:00:38,200
Oh, Teacher!

781
01:00:38,200 --> 01:00:40,250
Hello.

782
01:00:49,250 --> 01:00:53,650
You have to live life until the end, you have to go until the end

783
01:00:53,650 --> 01:00:57,280
to find the meaning of life given to you.

784
01:00:57,280 --> 01:01:00,420
You have to go until the end.
